canonical:
  title: 賀皇太子正位箋
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 立嫡正儲以端國本承祧主鬯允協輿情凡在見聞莫不蹈舞恭惟凝姿岐嶷禀性溫文篤親賢好學之誠克全三善勤視膳問安之節祗奉兩宮基萬世之大平在一人之有慶瑤圖永固海宇同懽伏念叨守弊封幸逢煕代重光日月獲囿照臨千歲岡陵倍申頌祝
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀皇太子正位箋
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 立嫡正儲。以端國本。承祧主鬯。允協輿情。凡在見聞。莫不蹈舞。恭惟凝姿岐嶷。禀性溫文。篤親賢好學之誠。克全三善。勤視膳問安之節。祗奉兩宮。基萬世之大平。在一人之有慶。瑤圖永固。海宇同懽。伏念叨守弊封。幸逢煕代。重光日月。獲囿照臨。千歲岡陵。倍申頌祝。
korean:
  title: 하 황태자 정위전
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 적자(嫡子)를 세워 태자를 삼아 국본(國本)을 단정(端正)케 하시고, 왕사(王嗣)를 이어 제사를 주장하여 진실로 여정(輿情)에 맞사오니, 무릇 보고 듣는 자가 모두 다 기뻐 춤추옵나이다. 공손히 생각하옵건대, 타고나신 용자(容姿)가 영특하시고 품성(稟性)이 온문(溫文)하시어, 어진 이를 친히하고 학문을 좋아하시는 독실한 정성은 능히 삼선(三善)을 온전히 하시고, 시선(視膳)과 문안(問安)의 절차를 부지런히 보살펴, 삼가 양궁(兩宮)을 받들어, 만세(萬世) 태평의 터를 이룩함이 한 분의 경사를 가지심에 있사오니, 황통(皇統)이 깊이 견고하고 온 세상이 함께 즐거워하나이다. 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 외람히 폐봉(弊封)을 지키면서 다행히 소대(昭代)를 만나, 겹쳐 빛나는 해와 달이 조림(照臨)하는 은혜를 받자옵고 천세(千歲) 강릉(岡陵)의 송축(頌祝)을 곱절로 올리나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0700&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Memorial Celebrating the Crown Prince's Ascension to the Rightful Succession
  author: Byeon Gye-ryang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    By establishing the rightful heir as Crown Prince, the foundation of the realm is made secure, and the succession of royal rites continues true—a course that accords perfectly with the wishes of all people. Indeed, all who hear and witness this rejoice and dance with gladness.

    I humbly reflect that Your Highness possesses an extraordinary countenance and a gentle, refined nature. Your sincere devotion to virtue and your earnest love of learning embody the three excellences in fullness, while your diligent attention to the royal meals and your reverent inquiries after the well-being of both Dowagers demonstrate filial piety and proper conduct. Thus the foundation for ten thousand years of great peace is established in the good fortune of one person. The imperial succession stands eternally firm, and all under heaven rejoices together.

    I, though unworthy, am blessed to guard this humble domain and fortunate to witness this glorious age. May the radiance of sun and moon illuminate all things, and I offer renewed prayers for the eternal glory of the ancestral tombs.
  footnotes:
    - This is a congratulatory memorial (箋) presented to the Chinese imperial court upon the establishment of a crown prince. Byeon Gye-ryang was a Goryeo official.
    - The 'three excellences' (三善) refers to virtue, wisdom, and filial piety.
    - The reference to 'both Dowagers' (兩宮) indicates the Queen Mother and another senior female member of the royal household.
    - '''Ancestral tombs'' (岡陵) is a metaphorical reference to eternal imperial continuity and ancestral veneration.'
